title: For Sale:  Rare WWII Vintage Carcano 6.5 Bolt Action Rifle
postcontent:
Italian make Carcano 6.5 military rifle. This is a short  37” version (17 inch barrel) that was manufactured as a carbine for special troops like mortar crews and motorcycle troops.  This gun was probably manufactured between 1940 and 1945. This example has obviously received some special treatment; the chrome trigger guard, butt plate, and bayonet mount may not be original features unless this was manufactured as a special ceremonial rifle or gift of some kind; which is possible but may be difficult to verify.  Special ceremonial versions were manufactured.  On the other hand I don’t know why someone would take the trouble to chrome plate these parts. If the chrome is an original feature, this is a very rare example. Actually, no matter how you look at it this is a rare example of a WWII era Carcano rifle. 

The rifle is in excellent condition and fully functional although it will need a good cleaning. These rifles also have excellent ballistic characteristics with muzzle velocities around 2,000 fps. The short barrel limits its effective range somewhat as far as hunting is concerned but I had good luck with it in the woods of Northern MN.

Here  are 3 Remington 700 .30 cal unchambered and unfinished barrels. They are 5R and 1-12 twist.  They have not been chambered or crowned or anything like that.
